<div class="crumbs">
  <a href="/index.html">Home</a> / <a href="/leagues.html">Leagues</a> / <span>NPB · Japan</span>
</div>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-flag">Japan · Nippon Professional Baseball · 2026 Season</div>
    <div class="hero-country">
      <span class="hero-flag-emoji">🇯🇵</span>
      <div>
        <div class="hero-title">NPB</div>
        <div class="hero-full">Nippon Professional Baseball · 日本野球機構</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      The <strong>second-best baseball league on Earth</strong> and the hardest to watch legally from the US — unless you know the trick. The <strong>Pacific League</strong> has a unified streaming deal. The <strong>Central League</strong> is fragmented by club. And the <strong>interleague window</strong> from May 26 to June 14 is the one time Giants, Tigers, and Carp games are streamable in America.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-stats">
      <div><div class="hs-num">12</div><div class="hs-lbl">Teams</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">143</div><div class="hs-lbl">Games / Team</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">2</div><div class="hs-lbl">Leagues</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">UTC+9</div><div class="hs-lbl">JST · ET +13</div></div>
      <div><div class="hs-num">1936</div><div class="hs-lbl">Founded</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="page">

  <div class="watch-window">
    <div class="ww-title">⚡ When to Watch NPB from the US</div>
    <div class="ww-lede">
      Most NPB games start at <strong>6:00 PM JST on weekdays</strong>, <strong>2:00 PM JST on weekends and holidays</strong>. Japan is UTC+9. That's <strong>-14 hours from ET</strong>. In practical terms, every weekday game is a 4:00 AM ET wake-up call. Weekend day games? 12:00 AM–1:00 AM ET — still late, but workable. <strong>Golden Week (May 3–5)</strong> is the best viewing window of the season.
    </div>
    <div class="ww-grid">
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">4:00 AM ET</div><div class="ww-lbl">Weekday 18:00 JST</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">12:00 AM ET</div><div class="ww-lbl">Weekend 14:00 JST</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">1:00 AM PT</div><div class="ww-lbl">Weekday West Coast</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">Sat–Sun</div><div class="ww-lbl">Best US window</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">May 3–5</div><div class="ww-lbl">Golden Week peak</div></div>
      <div class="ww-item"><div class="ww-val">May 26–Jun 14</div><div class="ww-lbl">Interleague window</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="watch-window purple">
    <div class="ww-title">🔑 The Interleague Hack — How to Watch Giants & Tigers in the US</div>
    <div class="ww-lede">
      Central League games (Yomiuri Giants, Hanshin Tigers, Hiroshima Carp, Yakult Swallows, DeNA BayStars, Chunichi Dragons) are <strong>mostly geoblocked outside Japan</strong>. But during the <strong>May 26 – June 14 interleague window</strong>, when a Central League team is the <em>road team</em> at a Pacific League park, those games ARE carried on Pacific League TV. That's your window. The best matchup to target: <strong>Giants vs. SoftBank Hawks at PayPay Dome</strong> — the two biggest brands in each league, on PLTV, streamable anywhere.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WHERE TO WATCH -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">01</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">Where to Watch NPB</h2>
      <span class="section-sub">US availability varies by league</span>
    </div>

    <div class="platforms">

      <div class="platform-card premium">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-primary">Pacific League · All 6 Teams</div>
        <div class="platform-name">Pacific League TV</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">~$11 / month (Americas)</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          The gold standard for international NPB fans. <strong>All six Pacific League clubs</strong>, live + on-demand, in English. Covers Hawks, Buffaloes, Marines, Eagles, Lions, Fighters. <strong>Free tier in EU/UK.</strong> During interleague play, Central League road games at PL parks are carried here too.
        </div>
        <a href="https://pacificleague.com/en/ptv" target="_blank" class="platform-link">pacificleague.com/en/ptv →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card premium">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-primary">US & Canada</div>
        <div class="platform-name">FTF / For The Fans</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Free (Roku / Pluto / Samsung)</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          <strong>English-language NPB replays</strong> on smart TV platforms. Not live, but same-day replays with Matt Garza and other ex-MLB commentators. Great for catching up without a 4 AM alarm.
        </div>
        <a href="https://ftflive.com" target="_blank" class="platform-link">ftflive.com →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card free">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-free">Free · 1 game/week</div>
        <div class="platform-name">YouTube — Pacific League</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">FREE</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Official Pacific League YouTube channel carries <strong>one free live game per week</strong> plus daily highlights. Search "Pacific League Baseball" — use this to sample before subscribing to PLTV.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card exclusive">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-exclusive">Central League · Per Club</div>
        <div class="platform-name">Giants TV / Tigers TV / Club Platforms</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Varies by team</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Central League rights are <strong>fragmented by club</strong>. Each team operates its own streaming service. Most are geoblocked to Japan. DAZN carries select CL content in some markets but availability is inconsistent team-to-team.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-primary">Spanish / Latin America</div>
        <div class="platform-name">DAZN (select markets)</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Varies</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          DAZN carries Central League content in a handful of international markets. Coverage is inconsistent — check locally.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="platform-card">
        <div class="platform-tag tag-primary">In Japan</div>
        <div class="platform-name">Rakuten TV / Paravi / DAZN JP</div>
        <div class="platform-cost">Domestic only</div>
        <div class="platform-desc">
          Full domestic coverage is available inside Japan via multiple platforms. Outside Japan, geoblocked.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- KEY DATES -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">02</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">2026 Season Key Dates</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Mar 27</div><div class="tl-title">Opening Day</div><div class="tl-desc">All 12 teams begin the 143-game regular season.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Apr 14–16</div><div class="tl-title">Traditional Series</div><div class="tl-desc">Hanshin Tigers vs. Yomiuri Giants — Japan's biggest rivalry.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">May 3–5</div><div class="tl-title">Golden Week</div><div class="tl-desc">Peak holiday attendance · day games · best US viewing window.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">May 26 – Jun 14</div><div class="tl-title">Interleague Play</div><div class="tl-desc">CL teams visit PL parks. CL road games streamable via PLTV.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Jul 20–23</div><div class="tl-title">Mazda All-Star Series</div><div class="tl-desc">Two-game All-Star Series · short schedule break.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">August</div><div class="tl-title">Koshien Displacement</div><div class="tl-desc">Hanshin Tigers play nearly all road games — Koshien hosts the high school tournament.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Late Sep</div><div class="tl-title">Regular Season Ends</div><div class="tl-desc">Pennant races close. Climax Series (playoffs) begin.</div></div>
      <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-date">Late Oct</div><div class="tl-title">Japan Series</div><div class="tl-desc">Best-of-7 championship between CL and PL champions.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TEAMS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-head">
      <span class="section-num">03</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The 12 Teams</h2>
      <span class="section-sub">Pacific + Central League</span>
    </div>

    <div class="divisions-wrap">

      <div class="div-block">
        <div class="div-title"><span class="div-league">Pacific League</span> · 6 Teams · On PLTV</div>
        <div class="div-teams">
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Fukuoka SoftBank Hawks</strong> — Mizuho PayPay Dome · Fukuoka</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Orix Buffaloes</strong> — Kyocera Dome · Osaka</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Chiba Lotte Marines</strong> — ZOZO Marine Stadium · Chiba</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Tohoku Rakuten Golden Eagles</strong> — Rakuten Mobile Park · Sendai</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Saitama Seibu Lions</strong> — Belluna Dome · Tokorozawa</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Hokkaido Nippon-Ham Fighters</strong> — ES CON Field · Sapporo</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="div-block">
        <div class="div-title"><span class="div-league central">Central League</span> · 6 Teams · Mostly Geoblocked</div>
        <div class="div-teams">
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Yomiuri Giants</strong> — Tokyo Dome · Tokyo · 22 titles</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Hanshin Tigers</strong> — Koshien Stadium · Nishinomiya</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Tokyo Yakult Swallows</strong> — Meiji Jingu Stadium · Tokyo</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Yokohama DeNA BayStars</strong> — Yokohama Stadium · Yokohama</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Chunichi Dragons</strong> — Vantelin Dome · Nagoya</div>
          <div class="team-row"><strong>Hiroshima Toyo Carp</strong> — Mazda Zoom-Zoom Stadium · Hiroshima</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DID YOU KNOW -->
  <div class="did-you-know">
    <div class="dyk-badge">The Fact</div>
    <div class="dyk-title">NPB Games Can End in a Tie — And Often Do</div>
    <div class="dyk-body">
      Unlike MLB, which eliminated ties decades ago and now uses the ghost runner in extras, <strong>NPB games can officially end in a tie after 12 innings</strong>. No zombie runner. No eternal extras. If it's tied after 12, it's a tie — and it counts in the standings. During the 2026 regular season, expect multiple series to feature ties that shift the pennant race. Combined with the <strong>Climax Series playoff format</strong> where the second-place team has to win a best-of-three just to reach the Japan Series, NPB's approach to "close games" is fundamentally different. It's baseball with <strong>more patience and less panic</strong>.
    </div>
  </div>

